1
00:00:14,317 --> 00:00:17,400
Let's say I did let
you live, right?

2
00:00:17,483 --> 00:00:21,025
You would develop civilization
just like before.

3
00:00:21,108 --> 00:00:23,692
Can you promise that
you won't do that?

4
00:00:24,858 --> 00:00:25,942
[SENKU chuckles]

5
00:00:26,025 --> 00:00:27,733
[SENKU]
The hell are you talking about?

6
00:00:27,817 --> 00:00:29,400
I could promise anything
to stay alive.

7
00:00:29,483 --> 00:00:32,400
No. You would never lie.

8
00:00:32,483 --> 00:00:34,525
Not when it comes to science.

9
00:00:36,900 --> 00:00:41,567
So will you promise me, here
and now, and for all eternity,

10
00:00:41,650 --> 00:00:43,900
that you'll abandon science?

11
00:00:46,650 --> 00:00:51,233
Because if you can make
that pledge, you can live.

12
00:00:51,317 --> 00:00:53,942
And then I won't be forced
into killing you.

13
00:00:56,817 --> 00:00:59,650
No, I can't. I can't do that.

14
00:01:05,775 --> 00:01:08,983
Of course not. I knew
that would be your answer.

15
00:01:10,358 --> 00:01:12,317
Just kill me in one blow.

16
00:01:12,400 --> 00:01:14,567
Because leaving me
to suffer till I die

17
00:01:14,650 --> 00:01:17,275
is both illogical
and inefficient.

18
00:01:18,400 --> 00:01:20,400
Don't worry, Senku.

19
00:01:20,483 --> 00:01:23,608
I'm going to sever
your cervical nerve.

20
00:01:23,692 --> 00:01:25,817
It'll be instantaneous.

21
00:01:25,900 --> 00:01:29,150
You'll be knocked unconscious
and die without suffering.

22
00:01:29,233 --> 00:01:30,525
I won't miss.

23
00:01:30,608 --> 00:01:32,067
[gasps]

24
00:01:32,150 --> 00:01:33,317
[YUZURIHA]
Taiju.

25
00:01:33,400 --> 00:01:35,025
[TAIJU gasps]

26
00:01:35,108 --> 00:01:39,400
Something's wrong.
I gotta get back, now!

27
00:01:39,483 --> 00:01:41,567
[TSUKASA]
Senku, I have a feeling

28
00:01:41,650 --> 00:01:44,942
that if we had met each
other 3,700 years ago...

29
00:01:45,025 --> 00:01:46,067
[ALL]
Huh?

30
00:01:46,150 --> 00:01:46,983
[ALL chuckling]

31
00:01:47,067 --> 00:01:48,650
[SENKU, TAIJU]
Huh?

32
00:01:48,733 --> 00:01:49,942
[SENKU screams]

33
00:01:50,025 --> 00:01:52,067
[yelling]

34
00:02:02,358 --> 00:02:04,858
[TSUKASA]
...before all this...

35
00:02:04,942 --> 00:02:08,025
...before the planet was
turned into a Stone World...

36
00:02:12,025 --> 00:02:13,400
[TSUKASA] ...I think that
you might have been

37
00:02:13,483 --> 00:02:15,525
my first real friend.

38
00:02:18,775 --> 00:02:21,108
[thud, squelching]

39
00:02:28,900 --> 00:02:31,858
[TAIJU screaming]

40
00:02:31,942 --> 00:02:36,025
Senku!

41
00:04:15,150 --> 00:04:17,775
[TAIJU screams]

42
00:04:17,858 --> 00:04:20,442
Senku!

43
00:04:20,525 --> 00:04:22,567
Please! Answer me, Senku!

44
00:04:22,650 --> 00:04:25,358
Open your eyes! Wake up
and say something!

45
00:04:25,442 --> 00:04:29,358
C'mon. This can't be right.
There's no way!

46
00:04:29,442 --> 00:04:31,317
Don't let it end
like this, Senku.

47
00:04:31,400 --> 00:04:34,275
After everything you've
done, you can't just die!

48
00:04:34,358 --> 00:04:36,900
Talk to me!

49
00:04:36,983 --> 00:04:40,358
I gave him a painless
death. It's over.

50
00:04:40,442 --> 00:04:42,233
I trust that as his friends,

51
00:04:42,317 --> 00:04:44,942
you will give him
a proper burial.

52
00:04:51,483 --> 00:04:52,567
[gasps]

53
00:04:54,525 --> 00:04:56,400
[TSUKASA]
Even if Taiju wasn't a pacifist,

54
00:04:56,483 --> 00:05:00,108
he'd never risk endangering
Yuzuriha by attacking me.

55
00:05:00,192 --> 00:05:03,942
That was the power
dynamic between us.

56
00:05:04,025 --> 00:05:07,983
But, Taiju, if Senku's death
sends you into a rage

57
00:05:08,067 --> 00:05:12,275
and drives you to
attack me mindlessly...

58
00:05:12,358 --> 00:05:14,692
...then I'll have
to kill you, too.

59
00:05:14,775 --> 00:05:17,942
Please, don't lose your head.

60
00:05:41,358 --> 00:05:43,275
What're you doing?

61
00:05:43,358 --> 00:05:46,525
[TAIJU] It's fine,
Yuzuriha. Don't worry.

62
00:05:46,608 --> 00:05:48,817
I'm still thinking clearly.

63
00:05:51,233 --> 00:05:52,733
[TSUKASA]
Of course.

64
00:05:52,817 --> 00:05:55,567
I have no choice but to fight.

65
00:05:55,650 --> 00:05:59,067
Sorry, Yuzuriha.
But I can only hope--

66
00:06:00,942 --> 00:06:04,650
[YUZURIHA]
No. It's okay, Taiju.

67
00:06:04,733 --> 00:06:08,650
After all, the three of us
made each other a promise.

68
00:06:08,733 --> 00:06:12,400
It'll all work out.
There's no doubt in my mind.

69
00:06:15,733 --> 00:06:19,025
Yeah. Thanks a lot, Yuzuriha.

70
00:06:19,108 --> 00:06:23,442
[TAIJU grunting]

71
00:06:23,525 --> 00:06:27,650
[TAIJU screaming]

72
00:06:29,400 --> 00:06:31,567
[TSUKASA]
Overhead? Why?

73
00:06:34,358 --> 00:06:36,775
[TSUKASA]
It must be a decoy.

74
00:06:36,858 --> 00:06:39,733
Good try, but I won't
fall for it, Taiju.

75
00:06:39,817 --> 00:06:42,525
No matter what you
do, you've lost.

76
00:06:42,608 --> 00:06:44,983
[TAIJU] Tsukasa's worried
I'll attack him.

77
00:06:45,067 --> 00:06:48,358
He won't dare take
his eyes off me!

78
00:06:48,442 --> 00:06:52,358
And that... is why
she has a chance!

79
00:06:54,942 --> 00:06:57,233
[YUZURIHA] Tsukasa thinks
I'm Taiju's weakness.

80
00:06:57,317 --> 00:06:58,942
Someone he has to protect.

81
00:06:59,025 --> 00:07:03,108
And in a primitive, stone world
like this one, it makes sense.

82
00:07:05,983 --> 00:07:09,067
[YUZURIHA]
But it's like Senku told us...

83
00:07:12,317 --> 00:07:16,608
[YUZURIHA, TAIJU] Science levels
the playing field for everyone!

84
00:07:29,067 --> 00:07:31,358
[TSUKASA]
That's black powder!

85
00:07:31,442 --> 00:07:33,608
[YUZURIHA] Senku didn't
leave us with nothing!

86
00:07:33,692 --> 00:07:37,192
[TAIJU] We have science
to remember him by!

87
00:07:37,275 --> 00:07:41,442
The three of us made a promise
to work together and stop you!

88
00:07:45,150 --> 00:07:50,525
[TAIJU] Me, Yuzuriha,
and Senku as well...

89
00:07:50,608 --> 00:07:53,067
...we're fighting
this battle together!

90
00:07:57,608 --> 00:08:00,025
Goodbye, Tsukasa!

91
00:08:43,858 --> 00:08:46,442
[TSUKASA] Taiju would
never attack anyone.

92
00:08:46,525 --> 00:08:49,317
Knowing that, I think he
must've expected me

93
00:08:49,400 --> 00:08:51,525
to come out of this unscathed.

94
00:08:52,942 --> 00:08:55,317
[TAIJU]
Goodby, Tsukasa!

95
00:08:58,233 --> 00:09:00,192
[TSUKASA]
So that's what he meant.

96
00:09:04,692 --> 00:09:08,233
It's gonna be okay, Senku.
You said it yourself, remember?

97
00:09:08,317 --> 00:09:11,567
If we're gonna run for it,
then we have to do it together!

98
00:09:11,650 --> 00:09:14,567
I don't care what anyone says--
you're not dying on me!

99
00:09:14,650 --> 00:09:16,650
I know you're alive!

100
00:09:16,733 --> 00:09:19,108
We've only just started
bringing back civilization,

101
00:09:19,192 --> 00:09:22,233
and you're not the kind of guy
to leave a job half done!

102
00:09:30,233 --> 00:09:32,483
[TSUKASA]
What's the point of fleeing?

103
00:09:35,483 --> 00:09:38,942
[TSUKASA] I know for a fact that
I severed his cervical nerve.

104
00:09:42,817 --> 00:09:45,317
[TSUKASA] There's no
coming back from that.

105
00:09:45,400 --> 00:09:48,942
Especially not in a Stone
World that has no medicine.

106
00:09:49,025 --> 00:09:50,983
[TAIJU] I'm trying to give
him a heart massage,

107
00:09:51,067 --> 00:09:53,067
but I have no idea
if I'm doing it right.

108
00:09:53,150 --> 00:09:56,275
But I can't do nothing,
and this is all I can think of.

109
00:09:57,275 --> 00:09:59,692
[TAIJU]
Wait! What about mouth to mouth?

110
00:10:01,150 --> 00:10:02,400
Ah! Hold on a second!

111
00:10:02,483 --> 00:10:04,900
I think we need to
keep his neck still!

112
00:10:04,983 --> 00:10:07,983
Because that's where
Tsukasa hit him.

113
00:10:08,067 --> 00:10:12,567
I'd been caught, and Senku
gave himself up for me.

114
00:10:15,900 --> 00:10:20,442
Wait, you're saying he
sacrificed himself?

115
00:10:20,525 --> 00:10:22,525
[STUDENT A] Check out
this psychology quiz.

116
00:10:22,608 --> 00:10:23,858
"There's been a tragic accident,

117
00:10:23,942 --> 00:10:26,442
and between your friend,
your lover, and yourself

118
00:10:26,525 --> 00:10:28,733
only one of you can be saved."

119
00:10:28,817 --> 00:10:30,150
Who would you choose?

120
00:10:30,233 --> 00:10:31,733
Uhh.

121
00:10:31,817 --> 00:10:34,275
I think I'd get stuck picking
between my friend and my lover.

122
00:10:34,358 --> 00:10:36,150
[STUDENT A] Might pick yourself
in the heat of the moment.

123
00:10:36,233 --> 00:10:37,942
How could anyone
make that choice?!

124
00:10:38,025 --> 00:10:40,358
This quiz of yours
seems kinda nasty.

125
00:10:40,442 --> 00:10:42,067
I choose everyone.

126
00:10:42,150 --> 00:10:44,150
[ALL gasp]

127
00:10:44,233 --> 00:10:47,233
[SENKU] I'd look for
a fundamental rule...

128
00:10:47,317 --> 00:10:50,025
...that'd let me save all of us.

129
00:10:50,108 --> 00:10:51,358
[YUZURIHA]
Guess that's the kind of answer

130
00:10:51,442 --> 00:10:53,983
you'd expect from the
Science Club's president.

131
00:10:54,067 --> 00:10:55,608
[TAIJU]
That's actually an option?

132
00:10:55,692 --> 00:10:57,442
Well, it's my choice, too, then!

133
00:10:57,525 --> 00:10:59,442
[STUDENT A] I think the point of
the question is more to reveal

134
00:10:59,525 --> 00:11:01,608
who's most important to you.

135
00:11:01,692 --> 00:11:03,817
[SENKU] That's ten billion
percent obvious.

136
00:11:03,900 --> 00:11:06,150
Your book belongs in the trash.

137
00:11:09,108 --> 00:11:11,483
[TAIJU] Senku wouldn't
go the suicide route.

138
00:11:11,567 --> 00:11:13,442
He wouldn't sacrifice anyone.

139
00:11:13,525 --> 00:11:16,900
He would stake the whole game
on the chance to save us all.

140
00:11:16,983 --> 00:11:19,983
We have to figure out
what he was thinking.

141
00:11:20,067 --> 00:11:23,317
If anyone can do it,
then it should be his friends!

142
00:11:23,400 --> 00:11:25,525
He must've left us a hint!

143
00:11:28,692 --> 00:11:30,275
His neck.

144
00:11:31,817 --> 00:11:34,108
Back at the hot spring,
when I was caught,

145
00:11:34,192 --> 00:11:36,817
Senku was drawing
attention to his neck.

146
00:11:36,900 --> 00:11:40,150
I think that's where he wanted
Tsukasa to strike him.

147
00:11:41,733 --> 00:11:43,067
[TAIJU]
You're right.

148
00:11:43,150 --> 00:11:47,442
That thing he was doing,
it's not a habit he always had.

149
00:11:47,525 --> 00:11:49,775
Why'd he keep touching
his neck and cracking it?

150
00:11:49,858 --> 00:11:52,150
Was he trying to
tell us something?

151
00:11:53,692 --> 00:11:55,108
[gasps]

152
00:11:55,192 --> 00:11:57,400
[YUZURIHA] There's a little bit
of stone left on his neck!

153
00:11:59,858 --> 00:12:01,233
Hold on.

154
00:12:01,317 --> 00:12:04,233
When we removed the stone
that was left on your foot,

155
00:12:04,317 --> 00:12:07,108
Senku told us something.

156
00:12:07,192 --> 00:12:08,733
That when we "de-petrified,"

157
00:12:08,817 --> 00:12:12,567
cracks were filled in
as part of the process.

158
00:12:12,650 --> 00:12:15,233
Here, Taiju! The revival fluid!

159
00:12:15,317 --> 00:12:16,358
[TAIJU]
Right.

160
00:12:19,025 --> 00:12:21,400
[YUZURIHA] It might work
on Senku's neck, too!

161
00:12:21,483 --> 00:12:23,400
There's a chance.

162
00:12:23,483 --> 00:12:28,150
Yeah, when he's de-petrified,
his neck might be fixed as well.

163
00:12:42,650 --> 00:12:44,358
The petrification's gone!

164
00:12:44,442 --> 00:12:46,275
[screams]

165
00:12:46,358 --> 00:12:47,858
Wake up, Senku!

166
00:12:47,942 --> 00:12:49,275
I knew you'd live!

167
00:12:49,358 --> 00:12:51,442
I knew you weren't gonna
let yourself be killed,

168
00:12:51,525 --> 00:12:54,067
not in a place like this!

169
00:12:54,150 --> 00:12:59,275
Senku, you're...
the star of hope.

170
00:12:59,358 --> 00:13:01,233
For humanity.

171
00:13:01,317 --> 00:13:04,400
For all of civilization!

172
00:13:04,483 --> 00:13:07,358
So please... come back!

173
00:13:07,442 --> 00:13:11,483
You have to wake up, Senku!

174
00:13:30,358 --> 00:13:35,025
[SENKU]
One, two, three, four,

175
00:13:35,108 --> 00:13:40,983
five, six, seven, eight, nine.

176
00:13:41,067 --> 00:13:42,733
Heh.

177
00:13:42,817 --> 00:13:43,983
All right.

178
00:13:44,067 --> 00:13:46,275
I can make it past
800,000 seconds

179
00:13:46,358 --> 00:13:49,233
without all-but losing
consciousness now.

180
00:13:49,317 --> 00:13:51,817
Guess my brain's
finally adjusting.

181
00:13:53,567 --> 00:13:54,567
[SENKU]
I've been frozen for

182
00:13:54,650 --> 00:14:01,358
117,354,889,550 seconds.

183
00:14:04,650 --> 00:14:10,858
[SENKU] So this is the
3,718th spring since I froze.

184
00:14:10,942 --> 00:14:12,942
Starting in spring
is an absolute must

185
00:14:13,025 --> 00:14:14,817
if I wanna survive.

186
00:14:16,858 --> 00:14:20,692
[SENKU]
Okay. No time like the present.

187
00:14:20,775 --> 00:14:23,983
Come on, me, get up.

188
00:14:24,067 --> 00:14:26,025
Get up.

189
00:14:26,108 --> 00:14:27,775
Get up, damn it!

190
00:14:27,858 --> 00:14:30,775
Get up! Get up!

191
00:14:38,067 --> 00:14:44,275
[SENKU breathing heavily]

192
00:14:44,358 --> 00:14:47,233
[chuckling]

193
00:14:47,317 --> 00:14:51,983
Yeah! I'm finally free!

194
00:14:52,067 --> 00:14:55,942
[SENKU] Yeah. A flashy entrance
like that would've been fun.

195
00:14:56,025 --> 00:14:57,567
[chuckles]

196
00:14:57,650 --> 00:14:59,150
[SENKU]
And I'm ten billion percent sure

197
00:14:59,233 --> 00:15:03,442
that's how my blockhead friend
Taiju would've done it.

198
00:15:03,525 --> 00:15:06,525
My first objective is to
evaluate my surroundings.

199
00:15:06,608 --> 00:15:08,275
I'll start with my own body.

200
00:15:08,358 --> 00:15:11,233
It can give me clues that're
worth its weight in gold.

201
00:15:13,775 --> 00:15:17,567
[SENKU] My initial location.
The position of my body.

202
00:15:17,650 --> 00:15:20,275
Even the order in which these
mysterious stone fragments

203
00:15:20,358 --> 00:15:22,525
fell off me.

204
00:15:22,608 --> 00:15:23,983
I'm gonna keep every last piece

205
00:15:24,067 --> 00:15:26,567
for when I'm ready
to investigate later.

206
00:15:27,608 --> 00:15:29,150
--[rustling]
--[gasps]

207
00:15:29,233 --> 00:15:31,858
[MONKEYS gibbering]

208
00:15:31,942 --> 00:15:33,942
[MONKEY C]
Yo. Where you from?

209
00:15:34,025 --> 00:15:35,983
Where's your monkey tribe?

210
00:15:39,442 --> 00:15:40,483
[grunts]

211
00:15:43,025 --> 00:15:44,900
[MONKEY C]
Dude's all smooth and shiny!

212
00:15:44,983 --> 00:15:47,650
Gross! What kinda monkey
has skin like that?

213
00:15:47,733 --> 00:15:50,025
[MONKEY A] He's got his
nasty peepee out, too!

214
00:15:50,108 --> 00:15:52,733
[MONKEY B] Well, so do
all of us, but still!

215
00:15:52,817 --> 00:15:55,025
[MONKEY C]
Gross!

216
00:15:56,567 --> 00:15:58,942
Am I the first human
they've seen?

217
00:16:05,483 --> 00:16:08,942
[SENKU] Doesn't look like
civilization survived.

218
00:16:09,025 --> 00:16:10,775
This is a whole new world.

219
00:16:10,858 --> 00:16:12,150
And from the looks of things,

220
00:16:12,233 --> 00:16:15,733
I might be the first shiny
monkey to be born in it.

221
00:16:15,817 --> 00:16:17,358
[chuckles]

222
00:16:17,442 --> 00:16:20,817
[SENKU] This is
exhilarating. Get excited.

223
00:16:28,025 --> 00:16:35,650
[SENKU] It's been
117,354,893,870 seconds now.

224
00:16:35,733 --> 00:16:38,650
Huh. This is some
nasty mental math.

225
00:16:38,733 --> 00:16:41,608
Especially when I factor
in the leap years.

226
00:16:41,692 --> 00:16:44,275
Not to mention the
earth's rotation slows

227
00:16:44,358 --> 00:16:47,400
by 17 millionths of
a second every year.

228
00:16:47,483 --> 00:16:49,817
That hardly adds up
to anything, though.

229
00:16:52,567 --> 00:16:56,983
[SENKU]
April 1st, 5738 A.D.

230
00:16:57,067 --> 00:16:59,650
Though you could
call this Year Zero.

231
00:16:59,733 --> 00:17:01,942
'Cause it all begins today!

232
00:17:09,525 --> 00:17:10,942
Tch.

233
00:17:11,025 --> 00:17:12,608
[chuckles]

234
00:17:12,692 --> 00:17:15,900
Behold the power of the
smooth and shiny monkey.

235
00:17:15,983 --> 00:17:18,858
My forebears had the
technology to reach space,

236
00:17:18,942 --> 00:17:22,150
and I'll rebuild their
civilization from scratch.

237
00:17:26,025 --> 00:17:31,525
[yelling]

238
00:17:34,358 --> 00:17:36,650
[MONKEY C] He's been rubbing
that stick this whole time.

239
00:17:36,733 --> 00:17:38,858
[MONKEY B]
That shiny monkey's a dumb-dumb.

240
00:17:38,942 --> 00:17:40,192
[MONKEY C]
Let's go home.

241
00:17:40,275 --> 00:17:42,067
[MONKEY B]
What a moron.

242
00:17:49,483 --> 00:17:51,775
[SENKU] I'm neither
a meathead like Taiju,

243
00:17:51,858 --> 00:17:55,317
nor an ultra-dextrous craft
club kid like Yuzuriha.

244
00:17:55,400 --> 00:17:56,733
There's no way
I can start a fire

245
00:17:56,817 --> 00:17:58,775
with nothing but a
primitive hand drill.

246
00:17:58,858 --> 00:18:00,692
Not in Japan's humidity.

247
00:18:02,900 --> 00:18:04,067
Heh.

248
00:18:08,108 --> 00:18:09,400
[SENKU]
That's right.

249
00:18:09,483 --> 00:18:13,983
This shiny monkey has
neither fangs nor claws.

250
00:18:14,067 --> 00:18:17,358
All I can do is improvise,
one step at a time.

251
00:18:17,442 --> 00:18:19,983
That's how
civilization advances.

252
00:18:28,775 --> 00:18:31,275
[screams]

253
00:18:31,358 --> 00:18:33,483
[MONKEY C] Why does he keep
smashing rocks like that?

254
00:18:33,567 --> 00:18:36,983
[MONKEY B] That shiny monkey's
definitely a dumb-dumb.

255
00:18:42,483 --> 00:18:43,650
[SENKU]
There's a trick to this,

256
00:18:43,733 --> 00:18:46,650
